A section of Modderfontein Road near Parkland Drive, in Esther Park, Kempton Park has been closed following a shootout between police and fleeing robbers a short while ago, Kempton Express reports.
Motorists are urged to avoid the area, as it is still an active crime scene.
READ MORE:Â Suspects arrested after shootout in Houghton
Ward councillor Tracey Lourenco said Sebenza SAPS told her the robbers were fleeing from Sandton and the chase went through Esther Park, ending close to Modderfontein Road.
Three suspects have been apprehended, while one was shot and wounded.

  
More information will follow, as this is a developing story.
